description.narrative: 2021 tested the implementation of the new DI policy framework. Two pilot municipalities managed to uphold the total moratorium on new placements in their residential childcare institutions. In addition, they successfully applied for the State Social Fund and obtained long-term (three years) financial commitment from the central government for alternative childcare services. As a result, 113 children and 59 families avoided unnecessary separation and institutionalization.;Technical assistance to 411 child protection practitioners across the sectors allowed to provide vital services to children in particular vulnerabilities, including UASC, repatriated, evacuated, and found in high-risk abuse, exploitation, and trafficking situations.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:20/01/2022
